    ns3:description """"Drink Alone Under the Moon; Raise a Wine Glass to Ask the Sky  are two installation works realized in 2019 by Wang Dongling . The artist used bright red acrylic on a six-fold screen of gold leaf to write two poems of Li Bai 李白 (701-762), namely "Drinking alone under the Moon (Yue xia duzhuo 月下独酌) and “Raise a Wine Glass to Ask the Sky" (Ba jiu wen tian 把酒问天) using his Chaos Script (luanshu 乱书) on a golden leaf screen of 1.7 meters high and 3.6 meters long. The screen is slightly folded and stands on a stainless steel plate of 1 meter wide and 4 meters long, so that the golden screen and the red writings reflect in it, mirroring and integrating  the viewers into the work in a continuosly changing dialogue with the artwork.
Wang Dongling used the same  two poems by Li Bai in 2016 when he realized a previous  hanging scroll with black ink on white paper, measuring  275cm×1870cm."""@en ;
