    ns3:description """In occasion of the opening performance of his solo exhibition “From Inception: Wang Dongling 60 Years of Calligraphy" (从头开始 ——王冬龄书法艺术60年), Wang Dongling created an innovative piece titled "From Inception" (Cong Tou Kai Shi 从头开始 ). The artist combined traditional tools and material, i.e. the brush and the black ink on xuan paper, with modern technology. The artist used a full-body motion capture system (全身动作捕捉系统), also known as mo-cap suit (motion capture suit). This wearable device recorded Wang's body movements, converting them into digital data to create a unique digital work. This blending of classical calligraphy with contemporary digital technology showcased Wang's pioneering approach and the dynamic evolution of his art form over six decades.
During the performance, 23 scrools forming the Dao De Jing have been used. These pieces consists of an installation featuring 23 massive scrolls with excerpts from the "Classic of the Way and Virtue" (Dao De Jing 道德经) written with black ink on xuan paper by the artist. These scrools, measuring 9 meters in length each and suspended at a height of 2.5 meters above the ground, descend from above and are arranged to create a visual reminiscent of an ancient forest of stone steles fallen from the sky. The monumental presence of these scrools with words of ancient wisdom imbues the space with a sense of vastness and weight."""@en ;
